<subSubSection id="BADD651FFFCFFFFF29F68A74FE51FABD" pageId="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F2783694FFCFFFFF29F68A74FE51FABD" blockId="17.[136,1452,158,1325]" pageId="17">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF29F68A74FED2FCA4" bold="true" box="[189,328,794,820]" pageId="17">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFCFFFFF282F8A74FD1CFCA4" authorityName="Zambrano &amp; Hagsater. A. Habit. B. Flower" authorityYear="2021" box="[356,646,794,820]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptopetalum">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF282F8A74FD1CFCA4" box="[356,646,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="17">Epidendrum leptopetalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the Nocturnum group, and is distinguished by the light green, oblong-elliptic to lanceolate leaves, yellow-green flowers with lip cream, long-acuminate sepals and petals, and the lip with hemi-ovate, slightly obtuse or truncate lateral lobes. The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFCFFFFF2DC58A0CFAF1FCEC" box="[1166,1387,866,892]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="litense">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2DC58A0CFAF1FCEC" box="[1166,1387,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="17">Epidendrum litense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="8AD07604FFCFFFFF286B8AE8FE1AFC30" box="[288,384,902,928]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. It differs in the green flowers with the lip white (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2AD28AE9FC22FC30" box="[921,952,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
yellow-green with the lip cream), the smaller dorsal sepal (
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF28568AC4FE02FC55" box="[285,408,938,965]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="31.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="28.0">28–35 mm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF28D48AC5FE24FC54" box="[415,446,939,964]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF288E8AC4FDA5FC55" box="[453,575,938,965]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="46.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="44.0">44–48 mm</quantity>
long), the 3-veined petals (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A3E8AC5FC0EFC54" box="[885,916,939,964]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
5-veined), the lip with triangular-falcate lateral lobes (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF299C8AA1FF6FFC78" box="[215,245,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
hemi-ovate), and the shorter column (7.0–8.0 mm 
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A028AA1FCFDFC78" box="[841,871,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
10.5–11.0 mm long). 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFCFFFFF2D278AA0FEC5FB9D" authority="Dodson (1977: 53)" authorityName="Dodson" authorityPageNumber="53" authorityYear="1977" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mininocturnum">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2D278AA0FA31FC78" box="[1132,1451,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="17">Epidendrum mininocturnum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96564B65FFCFFFFF29C38A9CFEC5FB9D" author="Dodson, C. H." box="[136,351,1010,1037]" pageId="17" pagination="48 - 56" refId="ref13621" refString="Dodson, C. H. (1977) New orchids from western Ecuador. Selbyana 2: 48 - 56." type="journal article" year="1977">Dodson (1977: 53)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Chocó region of 
<collectingCountry id="8AD07604FFCFFFFF2BDD8A9CFC9EFB9C" box="[662,772,1010,1036]" name="Colombia" pageId="17">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="8AD07604FFCFFFFF2A748A9CFC04FB9C" box="[831,926,1010,1036]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, differs in the smaller plants (less than 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF2C2F8A9CFA31FB9D" box="[1380,1451,1010,1037]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="17" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF29C38D79FF3DFBA0" box="[136,167,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
up to 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF29B98D78FEA3FBA1" box="[242,313,1046,1073]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="17" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
tall), flowers reddish-green to pink with a white lip (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2AD78D79FC21FBA0" box="[924,955,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
yellow-green with a cream lip), the shorter dorsal sepal (
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF28508D54FE0CFBC5" box="[283,406,1082,1109]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28 mm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF28D78D55FE21FBC4" box="[412,443,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF288A8D54FDA0FBC5" box="[449,570,1082,1109]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="46.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="44.0">44–48 mm</quantity>
long), the 3-veined petals (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A268D55FC11FBC4" box="[877,907,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
5-veined), and the lip with obliquely semi-ovate lateral lobes (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF28688D31FEDBFBE8" box="[291,321,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
hemi-ovate) (
<bibRefCitation id="96564B65FFCFFFFF28AB8D30FC97FBE8" author="Sanchez, L. &amp; Hagsater, E." box="[480,781,1118,1144]" pageId="17" pagination="1357" refId="ref15921" refString="Sanchez, L. &amp; Hagsater, E. (2010) Epidendrum mininocturnum Dodson. The genus Epidendrum, Part 9. Icones Orchidacearum 13: pl. 1357. [Instituto Chinoin, Mexico]." type="journal article" year="2010">Sánchez &amp; Hágsater 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFCFFFFF2A6A8D30FA32FBE8" authority="Hagsater &amp; Tobar (2018 a" authorityName="Hagsater &amp; Tobar" authorityYear="2018" box="[801,1448,1118,1144]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="condornocturnum">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A6A8D30FBE6FBE8" box="[801,1148,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="17">Epidendrum condornocturnum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96564B65FFCFFFFF2DCF8D30FA32FBE8" author="Hagsater, E. &amp; Tobar, F." box="[1156,1448,1118,1144]" pageId="17" pagination="1613" refId="ref15245" refString="Hagsater, E. &amp; Tobar, F. (2018 a) Epidendrum condornocturnum Hagsater &amp; Tobar. In: Hagsater, E. &amp; Santiago, E. (Eds.) The genus Epidendrum, Part 12. Icones Orchidacearum 16 (1): pl. 1613. [Instituto Chinoin, Mexico]" type="journal article" year="2018">Hágsater &amp; Tobar (2018a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: pl. 1613), restricted to the southeast of 
<collectingCountry id="8AD07604FFCFFFFF2B198DECFD35FB0C" box="[594,687,1154,1180]" name="Ecuador" pageId="17">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and possibly 
<collectingCountry id="8AD07604FFCFFFFF2A198DEDFC12FB0D" box="[850,904,1155,1181]" name="Peru" pageId="17">Peru</collectingCountry>
, can be distinguished by the elliptic leaves (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2CC68DEDFA31FB0C" box="[1421,1451,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
oblong-elliptic to lanceolate), larger petals (67–87 × 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF2B998DC8FCB4FB51" box="[722,814,1190,1217]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A7F8DC9FCC8FB50" box="[820,850,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
44 
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2A3E8DC9FC19FB50" box="[885,899,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="17">–</emphasis>
46 × 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF2AF08DC8FBDFFB51" box="[955,1093,1190,1217]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="2.1" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.4 mm</quantity>
), larger lip (longer than 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF2C1B8DC8FA1CFB51" box="[1360,1414,1190,1217]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2CC68DC9FA31FB50" box="[1421,1451,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
shorter than 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF285E8DA4FEFCFB75" box="[277,358,1226,1253]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="17" unit="cm" value="3.9">3.9 cm</quantity>
), with larger, hemi-elliptic calli (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2B928DA5FD6AFB74" box="[729,752,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs</emphasis>
. small, elliptic-ovate calli), the narrowly hemi-obovate lateral lobes, half as long as the mid-lobe (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF2B598D81FDAAFA98" box="[530,560,1263,1288]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
hemi-ovate, one third the length of the mid lobe), and the longer column (
<quantity id="353F9B71FFCFFFFF2C2F8D80FF2EFABD" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="17" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18 mm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFCFFFFF29F08C7DFF43FABC" box="[187,217,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="17">vs.</emphasis>
10.5–11.0 mm long).
